SendMessage
public abstract class MultimodalDialogInterpreter
extends DialogInterpreter

Interprets a multimodal dialog in which the oral and visual modalities are synchronized. The oral dialog is controlled using a restricted VXML file (see chapter 5), in which each field is linked to an element in the GUI (as explained in chapter 7)

Version:
1.3, 08/18/13
Author:
Zoraida Callejas, Michael McTear

oralToGui

public void oralToGui(Field oralField)
               throws MultimodalException
Synchronizes the oral and visual modalities in the direction: oral -> visual. That is, it can be used to fill a visual element when its corresponding oral field has been filled
